==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Quillaia bark
<hw>Quil*la"ia bark`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The bark
of a rosaceous tree (<spn>Quillaja Saponaria</spn>), native of Chile.
The bark is finely laminated, and very heavy with alkaline substances,
and is used commonly by the Chileans instead of soap. Also called
<altname>soap bark</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quillback</ent>⟦br⟧
